title: Grateful Dead Live at USAir Arena on 1994-10-09
description:
Hell In A Bucket, Bertha, Spoonful, Stagger Lee, Broken Arrow, Me & My Uncle->@, Big River@, So Many Roads, Promised Land Here Comes Sunshine, Samson & Delilah, Way to Go Home, Ship of Fools, Saint Of Circumstance-> Drums->Miracle->Comes A Time*->Throwing Stones->Lovelight

E: Rain

reviews.review_text: Slight freak out The show was good not great.  Had some good nugs of songs I liked, Broken Arrow, SMR, Rain, Comes a Time was a nice nodule.  I know we are supposed to stick to issues pertaining to the show and the sound quality, but I think this loosely aligns with the requirements.  We had really bad seats.  Typical Cap Centre or now US Air whatever.  So we have our party favors and everyone is in a real mellow focused mood.  Then my friend Ed says that there is something on Bobbys head.  So we look and wonder and look and wonder, and none of us can figure it out until somebody says "Oh my god, thats his hair and he has a bald spot.  WTF.  Good looking Bobby, the prepster, oh man.  It hits us all.  We all turn around to each other and just do not say another world about it.  You could basically hear everyone contemplating their own mortality at that time.  Put a strange mood on the ride home.

Landover 1994 This was one of the better shows of the Fall Tour.  Comes A Time is terrific to hear.  If you are a fan of this song, the show is worth the download. Sound quality is solid, but the performance is lacking in some areas.  Enjoy!

10-9-94 This is the last Comes A Time the boys ever played. From 87 to 95, they only did this tune 6 times live. With the exception of a handful of tunes in the first set, and the Comes A Time, I would say this show is pretty average in terms of performance in my opinion.

Little Did I know My friends and me at times were so sick of Liberty and So Many Roads during the 90's. I was not so upset when it came to SMR though because it seemed that Jerry almost always nailed it and I wasn't seeing the sad meltdowns that were becoming so ever more prsent. Now I can hear his pain all the more and can be happy that he found his Road and not so selfish as I was back then. Little did I know This night was nice for Phil also with a great sounding voice during Broken arrow and a much appreciated Lyric flub by one of the band members. I was just a decision away from going to this show and canceled at the last minuet. Sadly, I only saw 3 show after this.

fall wonder The last comes a time  ever so here it is and i remember the drive from philly decided to see one more show before i head back to Toronto. It was a sunday night and of course the cap centre is always heatty which puts alot of people on edge needless to say they played a decent show. The show shows the Deadstill have it even in 94 which was a solid year. This would be the last fall tour and for me one to remember because i saw at least one show every stop they made. It would just so have it that they would announce 3 shows in Toronto next fall only to have jer die before playing my home town since festival express. I must say following and touring with the Dead were some of the best times of my life. I miss all you guys.
Thanks Listening to Comes a Time ... so touching considering this is the last time they played it ... and wanted to mention I really enjoyed all your comments on this one ... thanks!

10-9-94 Good performance. Nice sound quality especially after the first few tracks or so. This is obviously a matrix recording. I've been checking out a lot of shows from '94 recently. I'm just reviewing the ones I think are good. Because of Jerry's' poor health and nasty habits some of these shows are real train wrecks.

Finally….Comes a Time Chased this for over 150 shows…
At my Brothers in NVA and missed 1st set…
Black Peter tease and hen the beautiful Comes a Time. Long live GD
